The paper presents a method for automatic latent fingerprint segmentation using a fully convolutional neural network and detection-based approach. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on forensic applications, which could fall under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves image analysis and pattern recognition, which could be associated with the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which could be associated with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
